30 // Adds S390-specific methods to convert InstructionOperands.
31 class S390OperandConverter final : public InstructionOperandConverter {
32  public:
33  S390OperandConverter(CodeGenerator* gen, Instruction* instr)
34  : InstructionOperandConverter(gen, instr) {}
35 
36  size_t OutputCount() { return instr_->OutputCount(); }
37 
38  bool Is64BitOperand(int index) {
39  return LocationOperand::cast(instr_->InputAt(index))->representation() ==
40  MachineRepresentation::kWord64;
41  }
42 
43  bool Is32BitOperand(int index) {
44  return LocationOperand::cast(instr_->InputAt(index))->representation() ==
45  MachineRepresentation::kWord32;
46  }
47 
48  bool CompareLogical() const {
49  switch (instr_->flags_condition()) {
50  case kUnsignedLessThan:
51  case kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
52  case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
53  case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
54  return true;
55  default:
56  return false;
57  }
58  UNREACHABLE();
59  }
60 
61  Operand InputImmediate(size_t index) {
62  Constant constant = ToConstant(instr_->InputAt(index));
63  switch (constant.type()) {
64  case Constant::kInt32:
65  return Operand(constant.ToInt32());
66  case Constant::kFloat32:
67  return Operand::EmbeddedNumber(constant.ToFloat32());
68  case Constant::kFloat64:
69  return Operand::EmbeddedNumber(constant.ToFloat64().value());
70  case Constant::kInt64:
71  return Operand(constant.ToInt64());
72  case Constant::kExternalReference:
73  return Operand(constant.ToExternalReference());
74  case Constant::kCompressedHeapObject:
75  case Constant::kHeapObject:
76  case Constant::kRpoNumber:
77  break;
78  }
79  UNREACHABLE();
80  }
81 
82  MemOperand MemoryOperand(AddressingMode* mode, size_t* first_index) {
83  const size_t index = *first_index;
84  if (mode) *mode = AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode());
85  switch (AddressingModeField::decode(instr_->opcode())) {
86  case kMode_None:
87  break;
88  case kMode_MR:
89  *first_index += 1;
90  return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), 0);
91  case kMode_MRI:
92  *first_index += 2;
93  return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputInt32(index + 1));
94  case kMode_MRR:
95  *first_index += 2;
96  return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputRegister(index + 1));
97  case kMode_MRRI:
98  *first_index += 3;
99  return MemOperand(InputRegister(index + 0), InputRegister(index + 1),
100  InputInt32(index + 2));
101  case kMode_Root:
102  *first_index += 1;
103  return MemOperand(kRootRegister, InputInt32(index));
104  }
105  UNREACHABLE();
106  }
107 
108  MemOperand MemoryOperand(AddressingMode* mode = nullptr,
109  size_t first_index = 0) {
110  return MemoryOperand(mode, &first_index);
111  }
112 
113  MemOperand ToMemOperand(InstructionOperand* op) const {
114  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(op);
115  DCHECK(op->IsStackSlot() || op->IsFPStackSlot());
116  return SlotToMemOperand(AllocatedOperand::cast(op)->index());
117  }
118 
119  MemOperand SlotToMemOperand(int slot) const {
120  FrameOffset offset = frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(slot);
121  return MemOperand(offset.from_stack_pointer() ? sp : fp, offset.offset());
122  }
123 
124  MemOperand InputStackSlot(size_t index) {
125  InstructionOperand* op = instr_->InputAt(index);
126  return SlotToMemOperand(AllocatedOperand::cast(op)->index());
127  }
128 
129  MemOperand InputStackSlot32(size_t index) {
130 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_S390X && !V8_TARGET_LITTLE_ENDIAN
131  // We want to read the 32-bits directly from memory
132  MemOperand mem = InputStackSlot(index);
133  return MemOperand(mem.rx(), mem.rb(), mem.offset() + 4);
134 #else
135  return InputStackSlot(index);
136 #endif
137  }
138 };
139 
140 static inline bool HasRegisterOutput(Instruction* instr, int index = 0) {
141  return instr->OutputCount() > 0 && instr->OutputAt(index)->IsRegister();
142 }
143 
144 static inline bool HasFPRegisterInput(Instruction* instr, int index) {
145  return instr->InputAt(index)->IsFPRegister();
146 }
147 
148 static inline bool HasRegisterInput(Instruction* instr, int index) {
149  return instr->InputAt(index)->IsRegister() ||
150  HasFPRegisterInput(instr, index);
151 }
152 
153 static inline bool HasImmediateInput(Instruction* instr, size_t index) {
154  return instr->InputAt(index)->IsImmediate();
155 }
156 
157 static inline bool HasFPStackSlotInput(Instruction* instr, size_t index) {
158  return instr->InputAt(index)->IsFPStackSlot();
159 }
160 
161 static inline bool HasStackSlotInput(Instruction* instr, size_t index) {
162  return instr->InputAt(index)->IsStackSlot() ||
163  HasFPStackSlotInput(instr, index);
164 }

168 class OutOfLineRecordWrite final : public OutOfLineCode {
169  public:
170  OutOfLineRecordWrite(CodeGenerator* gen, Register object, MemOperand operand,
171  Register value, Register scratch0, Register scratch1,
172  RecordWriteMode mode, StubCallMode stub_mode,
173  UnwindingInfoWriter* unwinding_info_writer)
174  : OutOfLineCode(gen),
175  object_(object),
176  operand_(operand),
177  value_(value),
178  scratch0_(scratch0),
179  scratch1_(scratch1),
180  mode_(mode),
181 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
182  stub_mode_(stub_mode),
183 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
184  must_save_lr_(!gen->frame_access_state()->has_frame()),
185  unwinding_info_writer_(unwinding_info_writer),
186  zone_(gen->zone()) {
187  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, scratch0, scratch1));
188  DCHECK(!AreAliased(value, scratch0, scratch1));
189  }
190 
191  void Generate() final {
192  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
193  __ DecompressTagged(value_, value_);
194  }
195  __ CheckPageFlag(value_, scratch0_,
196  MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask, eq,
197  exit());
198  __ lay(scratch1_, operand_);
199  SaveFPRegsMode const save_fp_mode = frame()->DidAllocateDoubleRegisters()
200  ? SaveFPRegsMode::kSave
201  : SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore;
202  if (must_save_lr_) {
203  // We need to save and restore r14 if the frame was elided.
204  __ Push(r14);
205  unwinding_info_writer_->MarkLinkRegisterOnTopOfStack(__ pc_offset());
206  }
207  if (mode_ == RecordWriteMode::kValueIsEphemeronKey) {
208  __ CallEphemeronKeyBarrier(object_, scratch1_, save_fp_mode);
209 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
210  } else if (stub_mode_ == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
211  __ CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object_, scratch1_, save_fp_mode,
212  StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub);
213 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
214  } else {
215  __ CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(object_, scratch1_, save_fp_mode);
216  }
217  if (must_save_lr_) {
218  // We need to save and restore r14 if the frame was elided.
219  __ Pop(r14);
220  unwinding_info_writer_->MarkPopLinkRegisterFromTopOfStack(__ pc_offset());
221  }
222  }
223 
224  private:
225  Register const object_;
226  MemOperand const operand_;
227  Register const value_;
228  Register const scratch0_;
229  Register const scratch1_;
230  RecordWriteMode const mode_;
231 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
232  StubCallMode stub_mode_;
233 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
234  bool must_save_lr_;
235  UnwindingInfoWriter* const unwinding_info_writer_;
236  Zone* zone_;
237 };

239 Condition FlagsConditionToCondition(FlagsCondition condition, ArchOpcode op) {
240  switch (condition) {
241  case kEqual:
242  return eq;
243  case kNotEqual:
244  return ne;
245  case kUnsignedLessThan:
246  // unsigned number never less than 0
247  if (op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord32 || op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord64)
248  return CC_NOP;
249  [[fallthrough]];
250  case kSignedLessThan:
251  return lt;
252  case kUnsignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
253  // unsigned number always greater than or equal 0
254  if (op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord32 || op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord64)
255  return CC_ALWAYS;
256  [[fallthrough]];
257  case kSignedGreaterThanOrEqual:
258  return ge;
259  case kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual:
260  // unsigned number never less than 0
261  if (op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord32 || op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord64)
262  return CC_EQ;
263  [[fallthrough]];
264  case kSignedLessThanOrEqual:
265  return le;
266  case kUnsignedGreaterThan:
267  // unsigned number always greater than or equal 0
268  if (op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord32 || op == kS390_LoadAndTestWord64)
269  return ne;
270  [[fallthrough]];
271  case kSignedGreaterThan:
272  return gt;
273  case kOverflow:
274  // Overflow checked for AddS64/SubS64 only.
275  switch (op) {
276  case kS390_Add32:
277  case kS390_Add64:
278  case kS390_Sub32:
279  case kS390_Sub64:
280  case kS390_Abs64:
281  case kS390_Abs32:
282  case kS390_Mul32:
283  case kS390_Mul64WithOverflow:
284  return overflow;
285  default:
286  break;
287  }
288  break;
289  case kNotOverflow:
290  switch (op) {
291  case kS390_Add32:
292  case kS390_Add64:
293  case kS390_Sub32:
294  case kS390_Sub64:
295  case kS390_Abs64:
296  case kS390_Abs32:
297  case kS390_Mul32:
298  case kS390_Mul64WithOverflow:
299  return nooverflow;
300  default:
301  break;
302  }
303  break;
304  default:
305  break;
306  }
307  UNREACHABLE();
308 }

311  ([&](int& ret) { \
312  AddressingMode mode = AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode()); \
313  MemOperand mem(r0); \
314  if (mode != kMode_None) { \
315  size_t first_index = (fi); \
316  mem = i.MemoryOperand(&mode, &first_index); \

321  return mem; \
322  })(ret)

439 template <int numOfOperand, class RType, class MType, class IType>
440 static inline int AssembleOp(Instruction* instr, RType r, MType m, IType i) {
441  AddressingMode mode = AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode());
442  if (mode != kMode_None || HasStackSlotInput(instr, numOfOperand - 1)) {
443  return m();
444  } else if (HasRegisterInput(instr, numOfOperand - 1)) {
445  return r();
446  } else if (HasImmediateInput(instr, numOfOperand - 1)) {
447  return i();
448  } else {
449  UNREACHABLE();
450  }
451 }

453 template <class _RR, class _RM, class _RI>
454 static inline int AssembleBinOp(Instruction* instr, _RR _rr, _RM _rm, _RI _ri) {
455  return AssembleOp<2>(instr, _rr, _rm, _ri);
456 }

458 template <class _R, class _M, class _I>
459 static inline int AssembleUnaryOp(Instruction* instr, _R _r, _M _m, _I _i) {
460  return AssembleOp<1>(instr, _r, _m, _i);
461 }

489 #define ASSEMBLE_COMPARE(cmp_instr, cmpl_instr) \
490  do { \
491  AddressingMode mode = AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode()); \
492  if (mode != kMode_None) { \
493  size_t first_index = 1; \
494  MemOperand operand = i.MemoryOperand(&mode, &first_index); \
495  if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
496  __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), operand); \
497  } else { \
498  __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), operand); \
499  } \
500  } else if (HasRegisterInput(instr, 1)) { \
501  if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
502  __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
503  } else { \
504  __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
505  } \
506  } else if (HasImmediateInput(instr, 1)) { \
507  if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
508  __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputImmediate(1)); \
509  } else { \
510  __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputImmediate(1)); \
511  } \
512  } else { \
513  DCHECK(HasStackSlotInput(instr, 1)); \
514  if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
515  __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputStackSlot(1)); \
516  } else { \
517  __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputStackSlot(1)); \
518  } \
519  } \
520  } while (0)
521 
522 #define ASSEMBLE_COMPARE32(cmp_instr, cmpl_instr) \
523  do { \
524  AddressingMode mode = AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode()); \
525  if (mode != kMode_None) { \
526  size_t first_index = 1; \
527  MemOperand operand = i.MemoryOperand(&mode, &first_index); \
528  if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
529  __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), operand); \
530  } else { \
531  __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), operand); \
532  } \
533  } else if (HasRegisterInput(instr, 1)) { \
534  if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
535  __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
536  } else { \
537  __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputRegister(1)); \
538  } \
539  } else if (HasImmediateInput(instr, 1)) { \
540  if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
541  __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputImmediate(1)); \
542  } else { \
543  __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputImmediate(1)); \
544  } \
545  } else { \
546  DCHECK(HasStackSlotInput(instr, 1)); \
547  if (i.CompareLogical()) { \
548  __ cmpl_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputStackSlot32(1)); \
549  } else { \
550  __ cmp_instr(i.InputRegister(0), i.InputStackSlot32(1)); \
551  } \
552  } \
553  } while (0)
554 
555 #define ASSEMBLE_FLOAT_COMPARE(cmp_rr_instr, cmp_rm_instr, load_instr) \
556  do { \
557  AddressingMode mode = AddressingModeField::decode(instr->opcode()); \
558  if (mode != kMode_None) { \
559  size_t first_index = 1; \
560  MemOperand operand = i.MemoryOperand(&mode, &first_index); \
561  __ cmp_rm_instr(i.InputDoubleRegister(0), operand); \
562  } else if (HasFPRegisterInput(instr, 1)) { \
563  __ cmp_rr_instr(i.InputDoubleRegister(0), i.InputDoubleRegister(1)); \
564  } else { \
565  USE(HasFPStackSlotInput); \
566  DCHECK(HasFPStackSlotInput(instr, 1)); \
567  MemOperand operand = i.InputStackSlot(1); \
568  if (operand.offset() >= 0) { \
569  __ cmp_rm_instr(i.InputDoubleRegister(0), operand); \
570  } else { \
571  __ load_instr(kScratchDoubleReg, operand); \
572  __ cmp_rr_instr(i.InputDoubleRegister(0), kScratchDoubleReg); \
573  } \
574  } \
575  } while (0)

577 // Divide instruction dr will implicity use register pair
578 // r0 & r1 below.
579 // R0:R1 = R1 / divisor - R0 remainder
580 // Copy remainder to output reg
581 #define ASSEMBLE_MODULO(div_instr, shift_instr) \
582  do { \
583  __ mov(r0, i.InputRegister(0)); \
584  __ shift_instr(r0, Operand(32)); \
585  __ div_instr(r0, i.InputRegister(1)); \
586  __ LoadU32(i.OutputRegister(), r0); \
587  } while (0)

589 #define ASSEMBLE_FLOAT_MODULO() \
590  do { \
591  FrameScope scope(masm(), StackFrame::MANUAL); \
592  __ Push(r2, r3, r4, r5); \
593  __ PrepareCallCFunction(0, 2, kScratchReg); \
594  __ MovToFloatParameters(i.InputDoubleRegister(0), \
595  i.InputDoubleRegister(1)); \
596  __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::mod_two_doubles_operation(), 0, 2); \
597  __ MovFromFloatResult(i.OutputDoubleRegister()); \
598  __ Pop(r2, r3, r4, r5); \
599  } while (0)

601 #define ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_UNOP(name) \
602  do { \
603  /* TODO(bmeurer): We should really get rid of this special instruction, */ \
604  /* and generate a CallAddress instruction instead. */ \
605  FrameScope scope(masm(), StackFrame::MANUAL); \
606  __ Push(r2, r3, r4, r5); \
607  __ PrepareCallCFunction(0, 1, kScratchReg); \
608  __ MovToFloatParameter(i.InputDoubleRegister(0)); \
609  __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::ieee754_##name##_function(), 0, 1); \
610  /* Move the result in the double result register. */ \
611  __ MovFromFloatResult(i.OutputDoubleRegister()); \
612  __ Pop(r2, r3, r4, r5); \
613  } while (0)

615 #define ASSEMBLE_IEEE754_BINOP(name) \
616  do { \

832  maybe_reverse_bytes) \

999 void FlushPendingPushRegisters(MacroAssembler* masm,
1000  FrameAccessState* frame_access_state,
1001  ZoneVector<Register>* pending_pushes) {
1002  switch (pending_pushes->size()) {
1003  case 0:
1004  break;
1005  case 1:
1006  masm->Push((*pending_pushes)[0]);
1007  break;
1008  case 2:
1009  masm->Push((*pending_pushes)[0], (*pending_pushes)[1]);
1010  break;
1011  case 3:
1012  masm->Push((*pending_pushes)[0], (*pending_pushes)[1],
1013  (*pending_pushes)[2]);
1014  break;
1015  default:
1016  UNREACHABLE();
1017  }
1018  frame_access_state->IncreaseSPDelta(pending_pushes->size());
1019  pending_pushes->clear();
1020 }
1021 
1022 void AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(
1023  MacroAssembler* masm, FrameAccessState* state, int new_slot_above_sp,
1024  ZoneVector<Register>* pending_pushes = nullptr,
1025  bool allow_shrinkage = true) {
1026  int current_sp_offset = state->GetSPToFPSlotCount() +
1027  StandardFrameConstants::kFixedSlotCountAboveFp;
1028  int stack_slot_delta = new_slot_above_sp - current_sp_offset;
1029  if (stack_slot_delta > 0) {
1030  if (pending_pushes != nullptr) {
1031  FlushPendingPushRegisters(masm, state, pending_pushes);
1032  }
1033  masm->AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(-stack_slot_delta * kSystemPointerSize));
1034  state->IncreaseSPDelta(stack_slot_delta);
1035  } else if (allow_shrinkage && stack_slot_delta < 0) {
1036  if (pending_pushes != nullptr) {
1037  FlushPendingPushRegisters(masm, state, pending_pushes);
1038  }
1039  masm->AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(-stack_slot_delta * kSystemPointerSize));
1040  state->IncreaseSPDelta(stack_slot_delta);
1041  }
1042 }

1046 void CodeGenerator::AssembleTailCallBeforeGap(Instruction* instr,
1047  int first_unused_slot_offset) {
1048  ZoneVector<MoveOperands*> pushes(zone());
1049  GetPushCompatibleMoves(instr, kRegisterPush, &pushes);
1050 
1051  if (!pushes.empty() &&
1052  (LocationOperand::cast(pushes.back()->destination()).index() + 1 ==
1053  first_unused_slot_offset)) {
1054  S390OperandConverter g(this, instr);
1055  ZoneVector<Register> pending_pushes(zone());
1056  for (auto move : pushes) {
1057  LocationOperand destination_location(
1058  LocationOperand::cast(move->destination()));
1059  InstructionOperand source(move->source());
1060  AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(
1061  masm(), frame_access_state(),
1062  destination_location.index() - pending_pushes.size(),
1063  &pending_pushes);
1064  // Pushes of non-register data types are not supported.
1065  DCHECK(source.IsRegister());
1066  LocationOperand source_location(LocationOperand::cast(source));
1067  pending_pushes.push_back(source_location.GetRegister());
1068  // TODO(arm): We can push more than 3 registers at once. Add support in
1069  // the macro-assembler for pushing a list of registers.
1070  if (pending_pushes.size() == 3) {
1071  FlushPendingPushRegisters(masm(), frame_access_state(),
1072  &pending_pushes);
1073  }
1074  move->Eliminate();
1075  }
1076  FlushPendingPushRegisters(masm(), frame_access_state(), &pending_pushes);
1077  }
1078  AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(masm(), frame_access_state(),
1079  first_unused_slot_offset, nullptr, false);
1080 }

1082 void CodeGenerator::AssembleTailCallAfterGap(Instruction* instr,

1084  AdjustStackPointerForTailCall(masm(), frame_access_state(),
1085  first_unused_slot_offset);
1086 }

1106 // Assembles an instruction after register allocation, producing machine code.
1107 CodeGenerator::CodeGenResult CodeGenerator::AssembleArchInstruction(
1108  Instruction* instr) {
1109  S390OperandConverter i(this, instr);
1110  ArchOpcode opcode = ArchOpcodeField::decode(instr->opcode());
1111 
1112  switch (opcode) {
1113  case kArchComment:
1114  __ RecordComment(reinterpret_cast<const char*>(i.InputInt64(0)),
1115  SourceLocation());
1116  break;
1117  case kArchCallCodeObject: {
1118  if (HasRegisterInput(instr, 0)) {
1119  Register reg = i.InputRegister(0);
1120  DCHECK_IMPLIES(
1121  instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister),
1122  reg == kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
1123  __ CallCodeObject(reg);
1124  } else {
1125  __ Call(i.InputCode(0), RelocInfo::CODE_TARGET);
1126  }
1127  RecordCallPosition(instr);
1128  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1129  break;
1130  }
1131  case kArchCallBuiltinPointer: {
1132  DCHECK(!instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate());
1133  Register builtin_index = i.InputRegister(0);
1134  Register target =
1135  instr->HasCallDescriptorFlag(CallDescriptor::kFixedTargetRegister)
1136  ? kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister
1137  : builtin_index;
1138  __ CallBuiltinByIndex(builtin_index, target);
1139  RecordCallPosition(instr);
1140  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1141  break;
1142  }
1143 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
1144  case kArchCallWasmFunction:
1145  case kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect: {
1146  // We must not share code targets for calls to builtins for wasm code, as
1147  // they might need to be patched individually.
1148  if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
1149  DCHECK_EQ(opcode, kArchCallWasmFunction);
1150  Constant constant = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(0));
1151  Address wasm_code = static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64());
1152  __ Call(wasm_code, constant.rmode());
1153  } else if (opcode == kArchCallWasmFunctionIndirect) {
1154  __ CallWasmCodePointer(i.InputRegister(0));
1155  } else {
1156  __ Call(i.InputRegister(0));
1157  }
1158  RecordCallPosition(instr);
1159  frame_access_state()->ClearSPDelta();
1160  break;
1161  }
1162  case kArchTailCallWasm:
1163  case kArchTailCallWasmIndirect: {
1164  // We must not share code targets for calls to builtins for wasm code, as
1165  // they might need to be patched individually.
1166  if (instr->InputAt(0)->IsImmediate()) {
1167  DCHECK_EQ(opcode, kArchTailCallWasm);
1168  Constant constant = i.ToConstant(instr->InputAt(0));
1169  Address wasm_code = static_cast<Address>(constant.ToInt64());
1170  __ Jump(wasm_code, constant.rmode());

1291  has_function_descriptor, &return_location);

1325  }

3259 // Assembles branches after an instruction.
3260 void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBranch(Instruction* instr, BranchInfo* branch) {
3261  S390OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3262  Label* tlabel = branch->true_label;
3263  Label* flabel = branch->false_label;
3264  ArchOpcode op = instr->arch_opcode();
3265  FlagsCondition condition = branch->condition;
3266 
3267  Condition cond = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition, op);
3268  if (op == kS390_CmpFloat || op == kS390_CmpDouble) {
3269  // check for unordered if necessary
3270  // Branching to flabel/tlabel according to what's expected by tests
3271  if (cond == le || cond == eq || cond == lt) {
3272  __ bunordered(flabel);
3273  } else if (cond == gt || cond == ne || cond == ge) {
3274  __ bunordered(tlabel);
3275  }

3279 }

3301  TrapId trap_id =
3302  static_cast<TrapId>(i.InputInt32(instr_->InputCount() - 1));

3307  void GenerateCallToTrap(TrapId trap_id) {
3308  gen_->AssembleSourcePosition(instr_);
3309  // A direct call to a wasm runtime stub defined in this module.
3310  // Just encode the stub index. This will be patched when the code
3311  // is added to the native module and copied into wasm code space.
3312  __ Call(static_cast<Address>(trap_id), RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
3313  ReferenceMap* reference_map =
3314  gen_->zone()->New<ReferenceMap>(gen_->zone());
3315  gen_->RecordSafepoint(reference_map);
3316  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3317  __ stop();
3318  }
3319  }
3320 
3321  Instruction* instr_;
3322  CodeGenerator* gen_;
3323  };
3324  auto ool = zone()->New<OutOfLineTrap>(this, instr);
3325  Label* tlabel = ool->entry();
3326  Label end;
3327 
3328  ArchOpcode op = instr->arch_opcode();
3329  Condition cond = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition, op);
3330  if (op == kS390_CmpFloat || op == kS390_CmpDouble) {
3331  // check for unordered if necessary
3332  if (cond == le || cond == eq || cond == lt) {
3333  __ bunordered(&end);
3334  } else if (cond == gt || cond == ne || cond == ge) {
3335  __ bunordered(tlabel);
3336  }
3337  }

3343 // Assembles boolean materializations after an instruction.
3344 void CodeGenerator::AssembleArchBoolean(Instruction* instr,
3345  FlagsCondition condition) {
3346  S390OperandConverter i(this, instr);
3347  ArchOpcode op = instr->arch_opcode();
3348  bool check_unordered = (op == kS390_CmpDouble || op == kS390_CmpFloat);
3349 
3350  // Overflow checked for add/sub only.
3351  DCHECK((condition != kOverflow && condition != kNotOverflow) ||
3352  (op == kS390_Add32 || op == kS390_Add64 || op == kS390_Sub32 ||
3353  op == kS390_Sub64 || op == kS390_Mul32 ||
3354  op == kS390_Mul64WithOverflow));
3355 
3356  // Materialize a full 32-bit 1 or 0 value. The result register is always the
3357  // last output of the instruction.
3358  DCHECK_NE(0u, instr->OutputCount());
3359  Register reg = i.OutputRegister(instr->OutputCount() - 1);
3360  Condition cond = FlagsConditionToCondition(condition, op);
3361  Label done;
3362  if (check_unordered) {
3363  __ mov(reg, (cond == eq || cond == le || cond == lt) ? Operand::Zero()
3364  : Operand(1));
3365  __ bunordered(&done);
3366  }
3367 
3368  // TODO(john.yan): use load imm high on condition here
3369  __ mov(reg, Operand::Zero());
3370  __ mov(kScratchReg, Operand(1));
3371  // locr is sufficient since reg's upper 32 is guarrantee to be 0
3372  __ locr(cond, reg, kScratchReg);
3373  __ bind(&done);
3374 }

3438 void CodeGenerator::AssembleConstructFrame() {
3439  auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
3440 
3441  if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
3442  if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
3443 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3444  if (info()->GetOutputStackFrameType() == StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY) {
3445  __ StubPrologue(StackFrame::C_WASM_ENTRY);
3446  // Reserve stack space for saving the c_entry_fp later.
3447  __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kSystemPointerSize));
3448 #else
3449  // For balance.
3450  if (false) {
3451 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3452  } else {
3453  __ Push(r14, fp);
3454  __ mov(fp, sp);
3455  }
3456  } else if (call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall()) {
3457  __ Prologue(ip);
3458  } else {
3459  StackFrame::Type type = info()->GetOutputStackFrameType();
3460  // TODO(mbrandy): Detect cases where ip is the entrypoint (for
3461  // efficient initialization of the constant pool pointer register).
3462  __ StubPrologue(type);
3463 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3464  if (call_descriptor->IsAnyWasmFunctionCall() ||
3465  call_descriptor->IsWasmImportWrapper() ||
3466  call_descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
3467  // For import wrappers and C-API functions, this stack slot is only used
3468  // for printing stack traces in V8. Also, it holds a WasmImportData
3469  // instead of the trusted instance data, which is taken care of in the
3470  // frames accessors.
3471  __ Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
3472  }
3473  if (call_descriptor->IsWasmCapiFunction()) {
3474  // Reserve space for saving the PC later.
3475  __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -kSystemPointerSize));
3476  }
3477 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3478  }
3479  unwinding_info_writer_.MarkFrameConstructed(__ pc_offset());
3480  }
3481 
3482  int required_slots =
3483  frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - frame()->GetFixedSlotCount();
3484  if (info()->is_osr()) {
3485  // TurboFan OSR-compiled functions cannot be entered directly.
3486  __ Abort(AbortReason::kShouldNotDirectlyEnterOsrFunction);
3487 
3488  // Unoptimized code jumps directly to this entrypoint while the unoptimized
3489  // frame is still on the stack. Optimized code uses OSR values directly from
3490  // the unoptimized frame. Thus, all that needs to be done is to allocate the
3491  // remaining stack slots.
3492  __ RecordComment("-- OSR entrypoint --");
3493  osr_pc_offset_ = __ pc_offset();
3494  required_slots -= osr_helper()->UnoptimizedFrameSlots();
3495  }
3496 
3497  const DoubleRegList saves_fp = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters();
3498  const RegList saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters();
3499 
3500  if (required_slots > 0) {
3501 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3502  if (info()->IsWasm() && required_slots * kSystemPointerSize > 4 * KB) {
3503  // For WebAssembly functions with big frames we have to do the stack
3504  // overflow check before we construct the frame. Otherwise we may not
3505  // have enough space on the stack to call the runtime for the stack
3506  // overflow.
3507  Label done;
3508 
3509  // If the frame is bigger than the stack, we throw the stack overflow
3510  // exception unconditionally. Thereby we can avoid the integer overflow
3511  // check in the condition code.
3512  if (required_slots * kSystemPointerSize < v8_flags.stack_size * KB) {
3513  Register stack_limit = r1;
3514  __ LoadStackLimit(stack_limit, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
3515  __ AddS64(stack_limit, stack_limit,
3516  Operand(required_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
3517  __ CmpU64(sp, stack_limit);
3518  __ bge(&done);
3519  }
3520 
3521  if (v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
3522  RegList regs_to_save;
3523  regs_to_save.set(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister());
3524  regs_to_save.set(
3525  WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister());
3526  for (auto reg : wasm::kGpParamRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
3527  __ MultiPush(regs_to_save);
3528  DoubleRegList fp_regs_to_save;
3529  for (auto reg : wasm::kFpParamRegisters) fp_regs_to_save.set(reg);
3530  __ MultiPushF64OrV128(fp_regs_to_save, r1);
3531  __ mov(WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::GapRegister(),
3532  Operand(required_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
3533  __ AddS64(
3534  WasmHandleStackOverflowDescriptor::FrameBaseRegister(), fp,
3535  Operand(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount() * kSystemPointerSize +
3536  CommonFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeAboveFp));
3537  __ CallBuiltin(Builtin::kWasmHandleStackOverflow);
3538  __ MultiPopF64OrV128(fp_regs_to_save, r1);
3539  __ MultiPop(regs_to_save);
3540  } else {
3541  __ Call(static_cast<intptr_t>(Builtin::kWasmStackOverflow),
3542  RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
3543  // The call does not return, hence we can ignore any references and just
3544  // define an empty safepoint.
3545  ReferenceMap* reference_map = zone()->New<ReferenceMap>(zone());
3546  RecordSafepoint(reference_map);
3547  if (v8_flags.debug_code) __ stop();
3548  }
3549 
3550  __ bind(&done);
3551  }
3552 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3553 
3554  // Skip callee-saved and return slots, which are pushed below.
3555  required_slots -= saves.Count();
3556  required_slots -= frame()->GetReturnSlotCount();
3557  required_slots -= (kDoubleSize / kSystemPointerSize) * saves_fp.Count();
3558  __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -required_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
3559  }
3560 
3561  // Save callee-saved Double registers.
3562  if (!saves_fp.is_empty()) {
3563  __ MultiPushDoubles(saves_fp);
3564  DCHECK_EQ(kNumCalleeSavedDoubles, saves_fp.Count());
3565  }
3566 
3567  // Save callee-saved registers.
3568  if (!saves.is_empty()) {
3569  __ MultiPush(saves);
3570  // register save area does not include the fp or constant pool pointer.
3571  }
3572 
3573  const int returns = frame()->GetReturnSlotCount();
3574  // Create space for returns.
3575  __ AllocateStackSpace(returns * kSystemPointerSize);
3576 
3577  if (!frame()->tagged_slots().IsEmpty()) {
3578  __ mov(kScratchReg, Operand(0));
3579  for (int spill_slot : frame()->tagged_slots()) {
3580  FrameOffset offset = frame_access_state()->GetFrameOffset(spill_slot);
3581  DCHECK(offset.from_frame_pointer());
3582  __ StoreU64(kScratchReg, MemOperand(fp, offset.offset()));
3583  }
3584  }
3585 }

3587 void CodeGenerator::AssembleReturn(InstructionOperand* additional_pop_count) {
3588  auto call_descriptor = linkage()->GetIncomingDescriptor();
3589 
3590  const int returns = frame()->GetReturnSlotCount();
3591  if (returns != 0) {
3592  // Create space for returns.
3593  __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, returns * kSystemPointerSize));
3594  }
3595 
3596  // Restore registers.
3597  const RegList saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters();
3598  if (!saves.is_empty()) {
3599  __ MultiPop(saves);
3600  }
3601 
3602  // Restore double registers.
3603  const DoubleRegList double_saves = call_descriptor->CalleeSavedFPRegisters();
3604  if (!double_saves.is_empty()) {
3605  __ MultiPopDoubles(double_saves);
3606  }
3607 
3608  unwinding_info_writer_.MarkBlockWillExit();
3609 
3610  S390OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3611  const int parameter_slots =
3612  static_cast<int>(call_descriptor->ParameterSlotCount());
3613 
3614  // {aditional_pop_count} is only greater than zero if {parameter_slots = 0}.
3615  // Check RawMachineAssembler::PopAndReturn.
3616  if (parameter_slots != 0) {
3617  if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate()) {
3618  DCHECK_EQ(g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32(), 0);
3619  } else if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
3620  __ CmpS64(g.ToRegister(additional_pop_count), Operand(0));
3621  __ Assert(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedAdditionalPopValue);
3622  }
3623  }
3624 
3625 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3626  if (call_descriptor->IsAnyWasmFunctionCall() &&
3627  v8_flags.experimental_wasm_growable_stacks) {
3628  {
3629  UseScratchRegisterScope temps{masm()};
3630  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3631  __ LoadU64(scratch,
3632  MemOperand(fp, TypedFrameConstants::kFrameTypeOffset));
3633  __ CmpU64(
3634  scratch,
3635  Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START)));
3636  }
3637  Label done;
3638  __ bne(&done);
3639  RegList regs_to_save;
3640  for (auto reg : wasm::kGpReturnRegisters) regs_to_save.set(reg);
3641  __ MultiPush(regs_to_save);
3642  DoubleRegList fp_regs_to_save;
3643  for (auto reg : wasm::kFpParamRegisters) fp_regs_to_save.set(reg);
3644  __ MultiPushF64OrV128(fp_regs_to_save, r1);
3645  __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], ExternalReference::isolate_address());
3646  __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, r0);
3647  __ CallCFunction(ExternalReference::wasm_shrink_stack(), 1);
3648  // Restore old FP. We don't need to restore old SP explicitly, because
3649  // it will be restored from FP in LeaveFrame before return.
3650  __ mov(fp, kReturnRegister0);
3651  __ MultiPopF64OrV128(fp_regs_to_save, r1);
3652  __ MultiPop(regs_to_save);
3653  __ bind(&done);
3654  }
3655 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
3656 
3657  Register argc_reg = r5;
3658  // Functions with JS linkage have at least one parameter (the receiver).
3659  // If {parameter_slots} == 0, it means it is a builtin with
3660  // kDontAdaptArgumentsSentinel, which takes care of JS arguments popping
3661  // itself.
3662  const bool drop_jsargs = parameter_slots != 0 &&
3663  frame_access_state()->has_frame() &&
3664  call_descriptor->IsJSFunctionCall();
3665 
3666  if (call_descriptor->IsCFunctionCall()) {
3667  AssembleDeconstructFrame();
3668  } else if (frame_access_state()->has_frame()) {
3669  // Canonicalize JSFunction return sites for now unless they have an variable
3670  // number of stack slot pops
3671  if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate() &&
3672  g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32() == 0) {
3673  if (return_label_.is_bound()) {
3674  __ b(&return_label_);
3675  return;
3676  } else {
3677  __ bind(&return_label_);
3678  }
3679  }
3680  if (drop_jsargs) {
3681  // Get the actual argument count.
3682  DCHECK(!call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters().has(argc_reg));
3683  __ LoadU64(argc_reg, MemOperand(fp, StandardFrameConstants::kArgCOffset));
3684  }
3685  AssembleDeconstructFrame();
3686  }
3687 
3688  if (drop_jsargs) {
3689  // We must pop all arguments from the stack (including the receiver).
3690  // The number of arguments without the receiver is
3691  // max(argc_reg, parameter_slots-1), and the receiver is added in
3692  // DropArguments().
3693  DCHECK(!call_descriptor->CalleeSavedRegisters().has(argc_reg));
3694  if (parameter_slots > 1) {
3695  Label skip;
3696  __ CmpS64(argc_reg, Operand(parameter_slots));
3697  __ bgt(&skip);
3698  __ mov(argc_reg, Operand(parameter_slots));
3699  __ bind(&skip);
3700  }
3701  __ DropArguments(argc_reg);
3702  } else if (additional_pop_count->IsImmediate()) {
3703  int additional_count = g.ToConstant(additional_pop_count).ToInt32();
3704  __ Drop(parameter_slots + additional_count);
3705  } else if (parameter_slots == 0) {
3706  __ Drop(g.ToRegister(additional_pop_count));
3707  } else {
3708  // {additional_pop_count} is guaranteed to be zero if {parameter_slots !=
3709  // 0}. Check RawMachineAssembler::PopAndReturn.
3710  __ Drop(parameter_slots);
3711  }
3712  __ Ret();
3713 }

3720 AllocatedOperand CodeGenerator::Push(InstructionOperand* source) {
3721  auto rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
3722  int new_slots = ElementSizeInPointers(rep);
3723  S390OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3724  int last_frame_slot_id =
3725  frame_access_state_->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - 1;
3726  int sp_delta = frame_access_state_->sp_delta();
3727  int slot_id = last_frame_slot_id + sp_delta + new_slots;
3728  AllocatedOperand stack_slot(LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep, slot_id);
3729  if (source->IsFloatStackSlot() || source->IsDoubleStackSlot()) {
3730  __ LoadU64(r1, g.ToMemOperand(source));
3731  __ Push(r1);
3732  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
3733  } else {
3734  // Bump the stack pointer and assemble the move.
3735  __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, -(new_slots * kSystemPointerSize)));
3736  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(new_slots);
3737  AssembleMove(source, &stack_slot);
3738  }
3739  temp_slots_ += new_slots;
3740  return stack_slot;
3741 }

3743 void CodeGenerator::Pop(InstructionOperand* dest, MachineRepresentation rep) {
3744  int dropped_slots = ElementSizeInPointers(rep);
3745  S390OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3746  if (dest->IsFloatStackSlot() || dest->IsDoubleStackSlot()) {
3747  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
3748  __ Pop(r1);
3749  __ StoreU64(r1, g.ToMemOperand(dest));
3750  } else {
3751  int last_frame_slot_id =
3752  frame_access_state_->frame()->GetTotalFrameSlotCount() - 1;
3753  int sp_delta = frame_access_state_->sp_delta();
3754  int slot_id = last_frame_slot_id + sp_delta;
3755  AllocatedOperand stack_slot(LocationOperand::STACK_SLOT, rep, slot_id);
3756  AssembleMove(&stack_slot, dest);
3757  frame_access_state()->IncreaseSPDelta(-dropped_slots);
3758  __ lay(sp, MemOperand(sp, dropped_slots * kSystemPointerSize));
3759  }
3760  temp_slots_ -= dropped_slots;
3761 }

3812 void CodeGenerator::AssembleMove(InstructionOperand* source,
3813  InstructionOperand* destination) {
3814  S390OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3815  // Dispatch on the source and destination operand kinds. Not all
3816  // combinations are possible.
3817  // If a move type needs the scratch register, this also needs to be recorded
3818  // in {SetPendingMove} to avoid conflicts with the gap resolver.
3819  if (source->IsRegister()) {
3820  DCHECK(destination->IsRegister() || destination->IsStackSlot());
3821  Register src = g.ToRegister(source);
3822  if (destination->IsRegister()) {
3823  __ Move(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
3824  } else {
3825  __ StoreU64(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3826  }
3827  } else if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
3828  DCHECK(destination->IsRegister() || destination->IsStackSlot());
3829  MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source);
3830  if (destination->IsRegister()) {
3831  __ LoadU64(g.ToRegister(destination), src);
3832  } else {
3833  Register temp = r1;
3834  __ LoadU64(temp, src, r0);
3835  __ StoreU64(temp, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3836  }
3837  } else if (source->IsConstant()) {
3838  Constant src = g.ToConstant(source);
3839  if (destination->IsRegister() || destination->IsStackSlot()) {
3840  Register dst = destination->IsRegister() ? g.ToRegister(destination) : r1;
3841  switch (src.type()) {
3842  case Constant::kInt32:
3843  __ mov(dst, Operand(src.ToInt32(), src.rmode()));
3844  break;
3845  case Constant::kInt64:
3846  __ mov(dst, Operand(src.ToInt64(), src.rmode()));
3847  break;
3848  case Constant::kFloat32:
3849  __ mov(dst, Operand::EmbeddedNumber(src.ToFloat32()));
3850  break;
3851  case Constant::kFloat64:
3852  __ mov(dst, Operand::EmbeddedNumber(src.ToFloat64().value()));
3853  break;
3854  case Constant::kExternalReference:
3855  __ Move(dst, src.ToExternalReference());
3856  break;
3857  case Constant::kHeapObject: {
3858  Handle<HeapObject> src_object = src.ToHeapObject();
3859  RootIndex index;
3860  if (IsMaterializableFromRoot(src_object, &index)) {
3861  __ LoadRoot(dst, index);
3862  } else {
3863  __ Move(dst, src_object);
3864  }
3865  break;
3866  }
3867  case Constant::kCompressedHeapObject: {
3868  Handle<HeapObject> src_object = src.ToHeapObject();
3869  RootIndex index;
3870  if (IsMaterializableFromRoot(src_object, &index)) {
3871  __ LoadTaggedRoot(dst, index);
3872  } else {
3873  __ Move(dst, src_object, RelocInfo::COMPRESSED_EMBEDDED_OBJECT);
3874  }
3875  break;
3876  }
3877  case Constant::kRpoNumber:
3878  UNREACHABLE(); // TODO(dcarney): loading RPO constants on S390.
3879  }
3880  if (destination->IsStackSlot()) {
3881  __ StoreU64(dst, g.ToMemOperand(destination), r0);
3882  }
3883  } else {
3884  DoubleRegister dst = destination->IsFPRegister()
3885  ? g.ToDoubleRegister(destination)
3886  : kScratchDoubleReg;
3887  double value = (src.type() == Constant::kFloat32)
3888  ? src.ToFloat32()
3889  : src.ToFloat64().value();
3890  if (src.type() == Constant::kFloat32) {
3891  __ LoadF32<float>(dst, src.ToFloat32(), r1);
3892  } else {
3893  __ LoadF64<double>(dst, value, r1);
3894  }
3895 
3896  if (destination->IsFloatStackSlot()) {
3897  __ StoreF32(dst, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3898  } else if (destination->IsDoubleStackSlot()) {
3899  __ StoreF64(dst, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3900  }
3901  }
3902  } else if (source->IsFPRegister()) {
3903  MachineRepresentation rep = LocationOperand::cast(source)->representation();
3904  if (rep == MachineRepresentation::kSimd128) {
3905  if (destination->IsSimd128Register()) {
3906  __ vlr(g.ToSimd128Register(destination), g.ToSimd128Register(source),
3907  Condition(0), Condition(0), Condition(0));
3908  } else {
3909  DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128StackSlot());
3910  __ StoreV128(g.ToSimd128Register(source), g.ToMemOperand(destination),
3911  r1);
3912  }
3913  } else {
3914  DoubleRegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
3915  if (destination->IsFPRegister()) {
3916  DoubleRegister dst = g.ToDoubleRegister(destination);
3917  __ Move(dst, src);
3918  } else {
3919  DCHECK(destination->IsFPStackSlot());
3920  LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(source);
3921  if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
3922  __ StoreF64(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3923  } else {
3924  __ StoreF32(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3925  }
3926  }
3927  }
3928  } else if (source->IsFPStackSlot()) {
3929  DCHECK(destination->IsFPRegister() || destination->IsFPStackSlot());
3930  MemOperand src = g.ToMemOperand(source);
3931  if (destination->IsFPRegister()) {
3932  LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(source);
3933  if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
3934  __ LoadF64(g.ToDoubleRegister(destination), src);
3935  } else if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
3936  __ LoadF32(g.ToDoubleRegister(destination), src);
3937  } else {
3938  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, op->representation());
3939  __ LoadV128(g.ToSimd128Register(destination), g.ToMemOperand(source),
3940  r1);
3941  }
3942  } else {
3943  LocationOperand* op = LocationOperand::cast(source);
3944  DoubleRegister temp = kScratchDoubleReg;
3945  if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat64) {
3946  __ LoadF64(temp, src);
3947  __ StoreF64(temp, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3948  } else if (op->representation() == MachineRepresentation::kFloat32) {
3949  __ LoadF32(temp, src);
3950  __ StoreF32(temp, g.ToMemOperand(destination));
3951  } else {
3952  DCHECK_EQ(MachineRepresentation::kSimd128, op->representation());
3953  __ LoadV128(kScratchDoubleReg, g.ToMemOperand(source), r1);
3954  __ StoreV128(kScratchDoubleReg, g.ToMemOperand(destination), r1);
3955  }
3956  }
3957  } else {
3958  UNREACHABLE();
3959  }
3960 }
3961 
3962 // Swaping contents in source and destination.
3963 // source and destination could be:
3964 // Register,
3965 // FloatRegister,
3966 // DoubleRegister,
3967 // StackSlot,
3968 // FloatStackSlot,
3969 // or DoubleStackSlot
3970 void CodeGenerator::AssembleSwap(InstructionOperand* source,
3971  InstructionOperand* destination) {
3972  S390OperandConverter g(this, nullptr);
3973  if (source->IsRegister()) {
3974  Register src = g.ToRegister(source);
3975  if (destination->IsRegister()) {
3976  __ SwapP(src, g.ToRegister(destination), kScratchReg);
3977  } else {
3978  DCHECK(destination->IsStackSlot());
3979  __ SwapP(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination), kScratchReg);
3980  }
3981  } else if (source->IsStackSlot()) {
3982  DCHECK(destination->IsStackSlot());
3983  __ SwapP(g.ToMemOperand(source), g.ToMemOperand(destination), kScratchReg,
3984  r0);
3985  } else if (source->IsFloatRegister()) {
3986  DoubleRegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
3987  if (destination->IsFloatRegister()) {
3988  __ SwapFloat32(src, g.ToDoubleRegister(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
3989  } else {
3990  DCHECK(destination->IsFloatStackSlot());
3991  __ SwapFloat32(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
3992  }
3993  } else if (source->IsDoubleRegister()) {
3994  DoubleRegister src = g.ToDoubleRegister(source);
3995  if (destination->IsDoubleRegister()) {
3996  __ SwapDouble(src, g.ToDoubleRegister(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
3997  } else {
3998  DCHECK(destination->IsDoubleStackSlot());
3999  __ SwapDouble(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
4000  }
4001  } else if (source->IsFloatStackSlot()) {
4002  DCHECK(destination->IsFloatStackSlot());
4003  __ SwapFloat32(g.ToMemOperand(source), g.ToMemOperand(destination),
4004  kScratchDoubleReg);
4005  } else if (source->IsDoubleStackSlot()) {
4006  DCHECK(destination->IsDoubleStackSlot());
4007  __ SwapDouble(g.ToMemOperand(source), g.ToMemOperand(destination),
4008  kScratchDoubleReg);
4009  } else if (source->IsSimd128Register()) {
4010  Simd128Register src = g.ToSimd128Register(source);
4011  if (destination->IsSimd128Register()) {
4012  __ SwapSimd128(src, g.ToSimd128Register(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
4013  } else {
4014  DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128StackSlot());
4015  __ SwapSimd128(src, g.ToMemOperand(destination), kScratchDoubleReg);
4016  }
4017  } else if (source->IsSimd128StackSlot()) {
4018  DCHECK(destination->IsSimd128StackSlot());
4019  __ SwapSimd128(g.ToMemOperand(source), g.ToMemOperand(destination),
4020  kScratchDoubleReg);
4021  } else {
4022  UNREACHABLE();
4023  }
4024 }
